        <!-- Release notes (keep it brief) -->
        <releasenotes>
            <![CDATA[
            <h3>Version 2.0.26 - Skip Score-Based Position During Intercept</h3>

            <h4>Bug Fix</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Don't use score-based position during intercept window</li>
                <li>Prevents score from overriding pending navigation target</li>
                <li>Better "l" field logging (distinguishes "at target" vs "not found")</li>
                <li>Both SCORM 1.2 and SCORM 2004 updated</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Technical Details</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Added inInterceptWindow check before score-based fallback</li>
                <li>Score represents furthest progress, not navigation intent</li>
                <li>Added foundField flag for better logging in suspend_data modification</li>
                <li>Maintains navigation accuracy during intercept period</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Previous Versions</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>v2.0.25: Prioritize "l" field over "resume" for position</li>
                <li>v2.0.24: Unlimited intercepts within 10s window</li>
                <li>v2.0.23: Skip suspend_data tracking during intercept</li>
                <li>v2.0.22: Re-enable write interception (l field only)</li>
            </ul>
            ]]>
        </releasenotes>
    </update>
